                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12735",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This still seems to be an issue. Look at the following example:\n\n{code}\n$date = new Zend_Date('2007-02-14', Zend_Date::ISO_8601);\n$date->addYear(1);\necho $date->getIso();\n{code}\n\nreturns 2008-02-14T00:00:00+01:00\n\nHowever, if we cross the end-of-february-border...\n\n{code}\n$date = new Zend_Date('2007-03-14', Zend_Date::ISO_8601);\n$date->addYear(1);\necho $date->getIso();\n{code}\n\nreturns 2008-03-13T00:00:00+01:0, which in my eyes is wrong.\n\nIf we add a year to 2008-03-14 (while 2008 being a leap year), it adds 366 days. Again, this is wrong. Somehow Zend_Date should take into account if it crosses the end of february border and not just calculate according to the base year.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-14T16:39:50.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-14T16:39:50.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12736",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Fixed with 3413.\n\nSomehow the change was undo... now it works.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-14T17:20:46.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-14T17:20:46.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12750",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thanks Thomas for fixing! It works fine now.\nJust please remove those two debugging lines:\n{code}\nIndex: library\/Zend\/Date.php\n===================================================================\n--- library\/Zend\/Date.php       (revision 3422)\n+++ library\/Zend\/Date.php       (working copy)\n@@ -1485,8 +1485,6 @@\n                         $date = $year - $date;\n                         $calc = 'set';\n                     }\n-print \"\\nOLD:$date\";\n-print \"\\nNEW:$year\";\n                     return $this->_assign($calc, $this->mktime(0, 0, 0, $month, $day, intval($date), true),\n                                                  $this->mktime(0, 0, 0, $month, $day, $year,         true));\n                 }\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=iezzip",
                        "name": "iezzip",
                        "displayName": "Philip Iezzi",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-02-15T06:07:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-02-15T06:07:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/12751",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This has already be done with SVN 3424 which solves ZF-912",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
